#. HTML: <section class="sutta" id="sn20.8"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "sn20.8:0.1"
msgid "Saṃyutta Nikāya 20 "
msgstr "Linked Discourses 20 "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn20.8:0.2"
msgid "1. Opammavagga "
msgstr "1. Similes "

#. HTML: </p><h1>
#. VAR: 8. Kaliṅgarasutta → kaliṅgarūpadhānasuttaṃ (bj)
msgctxt "sn20.8:0.3"
msgid "8. Kaliṅgarasutta "
msgstr "8. Wood Blocks "

#. HTML: </h1></div><p><span class="evam">
#. REF: sc1
msgctxt "sn20.8:1.1"
msgid "Evaṃ me sutaṃ—"
msgstr "So I have heard. "

#. HTML: </span>
msgctxt "sn20.8:1.2"
msgid "ekaṃ samayaṃ bhagavā vesāliyaṃ viharati mahāvane kūṭāgārasālāyaṃ. "
msgstr "At one time the Buddha was staying near Vesālī, at the Great Wood, in the hall with the peaked roof. "

msgctxt "sn20.8:1.3"
msgid "Tatra kho bhagavā bhikkhū āmantesi: "
msgstr "There the Buddha addressed the mendicants, "

msgctxt "sn20.8:1.4"
msgid "“bhikkhavo”ti. "
msgstr "“Mendicants!” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn20.8:1.5"
msgid "“Bhadante”ti te bhikkhū bhagavato paccassosuṃ. "
msgstr "“Venerable sir,” they replied. "

msgctxt "sn20.8:1.6"
msgid "Bhagavā etadavoca: "
msgstr "The Buddha said this: "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli2.268, sc2
msgctxt "sn20.8:2.1"
msgid "“Kaliṅgarūpadhānā, bhikkhave, etarahi licchavī viharanti appamattā ātāpino upāsanasmiṃ. "
msgstr "“Mendicants, these days the Licchavis live using wood blocks as pillows, and they exercise diligently and keenly. "

msgctxt "sn20.8:2.2"
msgid "Tesaṃ rājā māgadho ajātasattu vedehiputto na labhati otāraṃ na labhati ārammaṇaṃ. "
msgstr "King Ajātasattu Vedehiputta of Magadha finds no vulnerability, he’s got no foothold. "

#. VAR: sukhumālā → sukhumā (mr)
#. VAR: mudutalunahatthapādā → mudutalāhatthapādā (s1-3, km) | mudutaluṇahatthapādā (pts1-2)
msgctxt "sn20.8:2.3"
msgid "Bhavissanti, bhikkhave, anāgatamaddhānaṃ licchavī sukhumālā mudutalunahatthapādā "
msgstr "But in the future the Licchavis will become delicate, with soft and tender hands and feet. "

#. VAR: tūlabibbohanāsu → tūlabimbohanādīsu (bj) | thūlabimbohanāsu (s1-3, km) | tulabimbohanāsu (pts1-2) | tūlabibbohanādīsu (mr)
msgctxt "sn20.8:2.4"
msgid "te mudukāsu seyyāsu tūlabibbohanāsu yāvasūriyuggamanā seyyaṃ kappissanti. "
msgstr "They’ll sleep on soft beds with down pillows until the sun comes up. "

msgctxt "sn20.8:2.5"
msgid "Tesaṃ rājā māgadho ajātasattu vedehiputto lacchati otāraṃ lacchati ārammaṇaṃ. "
msgstr "King Ajātasattu Vedehiputta of Magadha will find a vulnerability, he’ll get his foothold. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc3
msgctxt "sn20.8:3.1"
msgid "Kaliṅgarūpadhānā, bhikkhave, etarahi bhikkhū viharanti appamattā ātāpino padhānasmiṃ. "
msgstr "These days the mendicants live using wood blocks as pillows, and they meditate diligently and keenly. "

msgctxt "sn20.8:3.2"
msgid "Tesaṃ māro pāpimā na labhati otāraṃ na labhati ārammaṇaṃ. "
msgstr "Māra the Wicked finds no vulnerability, he's got no foothold. "

msgctxt "sn20.8:3.3"
msgid "Bhavissanti, bhikkhave, anāgatamaddhānaṃ bhikkhū sukhumā mudutalunahatthapādā. "
msgstr "But in the future the mendicants will become delicate, with soft and tender hands and feet. "

msgctxt "sn20.8:3.4"
msgid "Te mudukāsu seyyāsu tūlabibbohanāsu yāvasūriyuggamanā seyyaṃ kappissanti. "
msgstr "They’ll sleep on soft beds with down pillows until the sun comes up. "

msgctxt "sn20.8:3.5"
msgid "Tesaṃ māro pāpimā lacchati otāraṃ lacchati ārammaṇaṃ. "
msgstr "Māra the Wicked will find a vulnerability and will get a foothold. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn20.8:3.6"
msgid "Tasmātiha, bhikkhave, evaṃ sikkhitabbaṃ: "
msgstr "So you should train like this: "

msgctxt "sn20.8:3.7"
msgid "‘kaliṅgarūpadhānā viharissāma appamattā ātāpino padhānasmin’ti. "
msgstr "‘We will live using wood blocks as pillows, and we will meditate diligently and keenly.’ "

msgctxt "sn20.8:3.8"
msgid "Evañhi vo, bhikkhave, sikkhitabban”ti. "
msgstr "That’s how you should train.” "

#. HTML: </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "sn20.8:3.9"
msgid "Aṭṭhamaṃ. "
msgstr ""

